14 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES AND THE SENATE OF THE
15 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
16 SECTION 1. The Secretary of State shall refer to the people for
17 their approval or rejection, as and in the manner provided by law,
18 the following proposed amendment to Section 13 of Article VI of the
19 Constitution of the State of Oklahoma to read as follows:
20 Section 13. A. The Governor shall commission all officers not
21 otherwise commissioned by law. All commissions shall run in the
22 name and by the authority of the "State of Oklahoma," be signed by
23 the Governor, sealed with the Great Seal of the State of Oklahoma,
24 and attested by the Secretary of State.
Req. No. 10733 Page 1

1 B. When any office shall become vacant, he shall, unless
2 otherwise provided by law, appoint a person to fill such vacancy,
3 who shall continue in office until a successor shall have been duly
4 elected or appointed, and qualified according to law.
5 C. If there is a vacancy in any statewide elected office, the
6 Governor shall appoint a person to fill the vacancy and such
7 appointee shall be subject to confirmation by a majority vote of
8 those elected to and constituting the State Senate.
